This paper deals with a variant of the bin packing problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of the algorithm's performance, which can be related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a two-phase approach suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT).
